    "created_at": "2016-09-28T11:30:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-28T11:30:24Z",
    "body": "This is because all windows share the same menu in OS X, so if you have multiple windows having one modal dialog won't block other windows.\n\nYou basically have two choices: 1) do not pass the window to dialog, so the dialog is not modal; 2) manually disable the menu.\n\nI'm closing this as won't fix since it is desired behavior.\n"
