    "created_at": "2016-10-03T18:36:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-03T18:36:46Z",
    "body": "I pass that parameter in both cases:\n\n```\n    const result = dialog.showOpenDialog(\n      this.mainWindow,\n      {\n        title: 'Select your 3D file',\n        filters: [\n            {name: '3D Models', extensions: ['stl','apf']},\n            {name: '3D Print Files', extensions: ['gcode', 'gco', 'g', 'x3g']}\n        ],\n        properties: [ 'openFile' ]\n      }\n    );\n```\n\nand \n\n```\n    dialog.showSaveDialog(\n      this.mainWindow,\n      {\n        title: title,\n        defaultPath: defaultName ? defaultName : null,\n        filters: filters\n      },\n      (filename) => {\n        evt.returnValue = filename ? filename : false;\n      }\n    );\n```\n\nso I still don't understand why they behave differently as it regards to the app native menu\n"
